item.title: Latest Design [Updated again with live view now!]
item.dc:creator: @ThAt0n36Uy Elijah
item.description:
@ThAt0n36Uy wrote:

I have to agree with Legit on this. There is no flow. It looks like you made it in 800x600 resolution. It’ll be hideous when converted to a full size website. Unless you make a bg for the content. So it’s not a fluid website, and a fixed width instead. That will also allow you to have a more uniform design.

For one thing the header needs some work. It should flow into the Navbar better than it is now. The navbar looks almost out of place. The footer of the website also needs some work, decrease the height of it, to like 20px. It’d look pretty good like that I think. having it run all the way across the page like it does now. And then have the content bg coming down to it, and somehow flowing into it. Maybe some sort of gradient. Or the footer overlaps the bottom of the bg, making it look like it goes behind it, add a small drop shadow above the footer.

The logo in the head needs to be fixed, move the text closer to the logo, put it maybe 9px away from the logo, at the same position on the header. Then maybe you could put a login form there, or a search bar. What you could do actually, is move all the links over to the left some more, and then place a search bar in the nav bar. Making the search right justified.

That’s just some of my ideas, they may or may not work. You don’t have to use them.
